Date: 1 Sep 2000 12:57:15 +0300
From: "Rubinstein" <rubins@inter.net.il>

Current outbreak of West Nile virus infection in Israel
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
27 human cases hospitalized in Israel have been identified this summer
(starting from the beginning of Jul until the end of Aug) as having West
Nile Fever on the basis of IgM antibodies in blood or CSF. Serological
testings were performed at the Central Virus Laboratories (The national
virus reference laboratories - headed by Dr. Ela Mendelsohn). The patients
suffered from encephalitis, meningoencephalitis and transverse myelitis.
Ages [of the patients are 30-85. Two of the patients have died.
--
Rubinstein
<rubins@inter.net.il>
