[2
Date: 2 Sep 2000 11:24:57 +0300
From: Manfred Green <m.green@trendline.co.il>

West Nile virus infection in Israel - immune status
---------------------------------------------------
In the report by Eleanor Kellon (31 Aug 2000) on West Nile Virus in Israel,
it is stated that most Israelis have acquired immunity against the disease.
This information has no basis in fact. In a serosurvey that my colleagues
and I conducted some years ago, about 40% of adults aged 40-55 (in 1982)
had antibodies, in adults aged 20-30 years old (in 1989) only 10% had
antibodies and about 7% of adults aged 18-19 years (in 1987) had
antibodies. According to these data, the overwhelming majority of Israelis
do not have antibodies against West Nile Virus.
Reference: Cohen D, Zaide Y, Karasenty E, Schwarz M, LeDuc JW, Slepon R,
Ksiazek TG, Shemer J, Green MS. Prevalence of antibodies to West Nile
fever, sandfly fever Sicilian, and sandfly fever Naples viruses in healthy
adults in Israel. Public Health Rev. 1999;27(1-3):217-30.
--
Manfred S. Green MD, PhD
Director,
Israel Center for Disease Control
<m.green@trendline.co.il>
